\displaystyle \exp\left(\frac{1}{n}\log\frac{1}{n!}\right) = \exp\left(-\frac{\log{n!}}{n}\right)
\lim_{n \to \infty}  \left(\frac{1}{n!}\right)^{1/n} = 0
\lim_{n \to \infty} \frac{\log{n!}}{n} = \infty
\ln n!=\sum_{k=1}^n\ln k\ge\int_1^n\ln x~dx\;.
